# UX flow patterns

Use two patterns consistently. Do not force one pattern everywhere.

## Full page (`/feature/new`, `/feature/:id/edit`)

Use when the user works on a **complex entity** for a while:

- Multiple sections, tabs, or economics
- Edit over several visits; shareable URL
- Examples: pedidos, productos/stock, clientes

Include header with title, short description, and "Volver a …" link.

## Transaction modal (`app-transaction-modal`)

Use for **quick actions from a list** — finish and return to the list:

- Short forms, few steps
- User keeps list context
- Examples: ventas, caja (ingreso/egreso), compras

```typescript
<app-transaction-modal
  [open]="modalOpen"
  title="..."
  subtitle="Acción rápida desde el listado. ..."
  (closed)="closeModal()">
  <!-- form -->
</app-transaction-modal>
```

Sub-flows inside a full page (pagos, costos extra en pedido) may use nested modals.

## Decision checklist

| Question | Page | Modal |
|----------|------|-------|
| ¿Se hace en segundos desde un listado? | | ✓ |
| ¿Tiene tabs, historial o economía detallada? | ✓ | |
| ¿Necesita URL para volver después? | ✓ | |
| ¿Es registrar un movimiento puntual? | | ✓ |

## Responsive (mobile-first)

- Page padding: `PAGE_SHELL_CLASS` (`p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8`) on list and form pages.
- Primary actions: `app-icon-action` or `ICON_ACTION_LINK_CLASS` — icon only on mobile, icon + label from `sm:` up. Always set `aria-label` and `title`.
- Tables: wrap in `TABLE_SCROLL_CLASS` with `TABLE_MIN_WIDTH_CLASS` for horizontal scroll on small screens.
- Navigation: sidebar is a drawer below `lg`; hamburger in topbar opens/closes it.
- Modals: use `app-transaction-modal` with `p-4 sm:p-6` inner padding.
- Form pages: stack header actions vertically on mobile (`flex-col sm:flex-row`).
